      • getArgIncludingPerhapsObjToInvokeOn

        public java.util.List<edu.stanford.nlp.sempre.Formula> getArgIncludingPerhapsObjToInvokeOn()
        Each element represents a Formula whose denotation is one of the arguments of the interface method (according to the order of the function's parameters). The first argument should be a denote a singleton containing the object on which the NLI method is to be invoked on if and only if DenotationUtils.firstArgumentIsObjToInvokeMethodOn(il.ac.technion.nlp.nli.core.method_call.MethodId) returns true for it.
